$interpreted: Dagger: Damn it, these Kingdom soldiers keep coming like flies!
Furygrowl: Careful!
Dagger: Still more?
Hyde: Captain Dagger, good work. We'll take over from here.
Hyde: Fellow soldiers, use formation six. Focus on driving the enemy back!
Furygrowl: Damn, I've no clue why we're going on the offensive now, actively provoking the Kingdom army...
Dagger: Like Hyde said, it's to figure out their position...
Furygrowl: But in the past month, the Bears have always been the ones charging head first, always the ones getting injured.
Furygrowl: The humans exploit our hard work and take everything for themselves. That seem fair to you?
Furygrowl: There've been rumors going around that humans are protecting their own. By weakening the Bears, the moment princess wins this war,
Furygrowl: she can turn against us while we're down and out!
Dagger: Don't spread such nonsense. Even if you don't trust Hyde's strategy, you should not suspect that Angelia has such malicious intentions!
Furygrowl: But we Bears are the ones getting injured, waiting to die!
Hyde: ...The basis of all strategies is to rely on the information you collected, then simulate and predict your opponent's tactics.
Angelia: What you are saying is that the amount of information one obtains essentially decides everything in war?
Hyde: What's really important is to let your opponent misjudge the information and leverage what you have.
Hyde: As long as your opponent is unable to read your hand and your true intentions, the outcome will naturally lean in your favor.
Angelia: ... I have benefited greatly from your teachings. Anything else I should pay attention to?
Hyde: "Have faith in your decisions; have doubt in everything else." Only then will you perceive the true...
Dagger: Angelia!
Angelia: Sir Dagger, what's the matter?
Dagger: Your battle plan for past month has caused frustration among quite a few Bear soldiers.
Dagger: You must stop this at once!
Angelia: This strategy was planned by Sir Hyde. We can't just change it all of a sudden...
Dagger: But only Bear soldiers are getting injured, can't you see?
Hyde: So far, we haven't let a single Bear soldier die. We took responsibility for treating the injured as well, didn't we?
Dagger: But...
Angelia: All in all, I trust Sir Hyde's strategy. If Sir Dagger has any problem with it, you have the right to withdraw from this operation.
